The police in KwaZulu-Natal are investigating a case of murder after an ANC official was shot dead. Branch secretary Sifiso Derrick Mlambo from Empembeni in Richards Bay was shot dead on Wednesday night, police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said. “It is alleged that Mlambo was asked by someone to deliver goods in the Empembeni area and as he was offloading the goods, an unknown man opened fire, fatally wounding him,” Mbhele said. -TNA Reporter